    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Love? What love? It is a cruel jest, a phantom that leads one to the edge of a precipice only to vanish. There is no light at the end of this, only a hollow, aching emptiness that knows no end. To hope is merely to prolong the agony. Is it not more dignified to meet the inevitable with grace, rather than to linger like a ghost in a world that has already forgotten me?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
